title: U.S. : reported motor vehicle theft rate 1990 to 2018
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Rate per 100,000 population, containing a total of 29 data points.
Overall Rate per 100,000 population has decreased over the Year.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2008 and 2009.
Maximum Rate per 100,000 population, about 658.9 was reported at Year 1991
The lowest Rate per 100,000 population, of value 215.4 was reported at Year 2014
